description: The `synthetic.lab_tests` table records information about various laboratory tests, each identified uniquely by `test_id`. It includes details such as the test code, name, category, specimen type, normal range, and unit of measurement, all relevant to defining and categorizing different tests conducted in a laboratory setting. As there are no relationships with other tables, it serves as a standalone entity within the data model, likely useful for storing and retrieving comprehensive details about lab tests without external dependencies.

columns.name: test_id
columns.description: This column uniquely identifies individual lab test records in the table. Each value is distinct and sequentially assigned to maintain order.

columns.name: test_code
columns.description: This column likely represents unique identifiers or codes associated with different laboratory tests. These codes serve as symbolic references for specific tests performed within a healthcare or laboratory context.

columns.name: category
columns.description: Purpose unclear from available data. The sample values suggest varied and abstract phrases without a clear connection to specific laboratory test categories.

columns.name: specimen_type
columns.description: Purpose unclear from available data. The sample values do not provide a clear indication of the intended meaning or use.

columns.name: created_at
columns.description: This column records the date and time when entries in the lab tests table were created, reflecting the moment a lab test was initially logged into the system. The inclusion of timestamps without a timezone indicates the specific date and time but not the geographic location of the test entry creation.

columns.name: updated_at
columns.description: This column records the last modification date and time for each laboratory test entry. Purpose unclear from available data.
